### Component Details

1. [External Cord]
   - Output: 30W (0.5 Wh over 60s) to Internal PSU (boot only)
   - Role: Initial power for system startup

2. [Internal PSU]
   - Input: 30W (boot only) from External Cord, 53W (12V) from TEG Hub post-boot
   - Output: 
     - 10.5W–26W to Motherboard
     - 195W–335W (5W min post-boot) to Heater
     - 0.5 Wh to Battery (boot)
     - 37.5W–22W to Charging Controller
   - Features: Relay switch cuts external cord when TEG output ≥ total demand

3. [Battery]
   - Specs: 12V, 7Ah, 84 Wh capacity (starts at 42 Wh, 41.5 Wh post-boot)
   - Input: 0.5 Wh (boot) from Internal PSU, 21.89W–37.38W from Charging Controller
   - Output: 
     - 10.5W–26W to Internal PSU (if TEG off)
     - 1W to maintenance loop (post-boot trickle charge)
   - Discharge Time (TEG off): 8h (10.5W), 4.54h (18.5W), 3.23h (26W)

4. [Charging Controller: TI BQ25792]
   - Input: 37.5W–22W from Internal PSU
   - Output: 21.89W–37.38W to Battery (99.5% efficiency, 0.073W–0.125W loss)
   - Role: Maintains battery charge; Charging Time: 1.13h (low), 1.44h (med), 1.93h (high)

5. [Motherboard: MSI B550M PRO-VDH]
   - Input: 10.5W–26W from Internal PSU or Battery
   - Output:
     - 2W–5W (self, dissipated locally)
     - 5W–65W to CPU
     - 0W–80W to GPU (capped within 26W total load)
     - 0.5W to RAM
     - 0.5W to SSD
     - 10W to Fan
     - 1W–5W to Magnet Regulator
   - Heat Output: 2W–5W (local dissipation)

6. [CPU: AMD Ryzen 5 5600X]
   - Input: 5W (low), 8W (med), 65W (high) from Motherboard
   - Output: 5W–65W (heat) to Copper Ferrofluid Tubes
   - Temp: 70°C–80°C max

7. [GPU: NVIDIA RTX 2060]
   - Input: 0W (low), 3W (med), 80W (high, capped within 26W total) from Motherboard
   - Output: 0W–80W (heat) to Copper Ferrofluid Tubes
   - Temp: 70°C–80°C max

8. [RAM: 1x8GB DDR4-2666]
   - Input: 0.5W from Motherboard
   - Output: 0.5W (heat, dissipated locally)

9. [SSD: Samsung 970 EVO 500GB]
   - Input: 0.5W from Motherboard
   - Output: 0.5W (heat, dissipated locally)

10. [Fan: 4000 cm² Fins]
    - Input: 10W (power) from Motherboard, 287W (waste heat) from TEG Hub
    - Role: Dissipates waste heat (4000 cm², ~70 W/m²·K convection + fan boost)

11. [Heater: Ohmite TGHGCR0010FE]
    - Input: 195W–335W (5W min post-boot) from Internal PSU
    - Output: 195W–335W (heat) to Magnet Regulator
    - Role: Balances heat to maintain 340W to TEG Hub

12. [Magnet Regulator]
    - Input: 1W–5W (power) from Motherboard, 5W–145W (heat) from CPU/GPU, 195W–335W (heat) from Heater
    - Output: Controls ferrofluid flow in Copper Ferrofluid Tubes (0.05–0.3 T field)
    - Sensor: Monitors CPU/GPU heat (5W–145W) for dynamic field adjustment

13. [Copper Ferrofluid Tubes]
    - Specs: 6 mm diameter, 20 cm length, copper, Ferrotec EFH1 ferrofluid (85°C max, refillable via port)
    - Input: 5W–145W (heat) from CPU/GPU, 195W–335W (heat) from Heater via Magnet Regulator
    - Output: 340W (heat @ 85°C) to Heat Exchanger
    - Flow: 3.15 cm³/s (11.1 cm/s velocity), driven by 1.06 N magnetic force vs. 0.62 N drag

14. [Heat Exchanger]
    - Specs: 227 cm² (15 cm x 15 cm), copper
    - Input: 340W (heat @ 85°C) from Copper Ferrofluid Tubes
    - Output: 340W (heat @ 100°C) to Copper Heat Pipes
    - Role: Protects ferrofluid from >90°C while boosting TEG input temp

15. [Copper Heat Pipes]
    - Specs: 6 mm diameter, 4x, sintered wick, copper
    - Input: 340W (heat @ 100°C) from Heat Exchanger
    - Output: 340W (heat) to TEG Hub
    - Capacity: ~50–100W per pipe, total >340W

16. [TEG Hub: 6x Kryotherm TGM]
    - Specs: 6x TGM-199-1.4-1.2 (48W) + 1x TGM-127-1.0-1.3 (5W), 15.6% efficiency
    - Input: 340W (heat @ 100°C hot side, 50°C cold side, ΔT = 50 K)
    - Output: 53W (12V) to Internal PSU, 287W (waste heat) to Fan

